On Cuban Independence Day, the United States recognizes the efforts of those who fought for Cuba's freedom and expresses solidarity with the Cuban people in their pursuit of fundamental rights. The US condemns Cuba's oppressive regime and supports the millions who have fled in search of a better life. The US advocates for a government in Cuba that promotes individual liberties, human rights, and prosperity. The US opposes Cuba's socialist model and aims to prevent the export of its repression. The US has implemented a strong policy towards Cuba that promotes human rights, free markets, and a transition to democracy. The US will continue to collaborate with allies and partners in the Western Hemisphere to bring stability, religious freedom, cooperation, and a brighter future for Cuba. The contributions of Cuban Americans to the American story are celebrated, and the US pledges to work with them to secure a better future for Cuba.